\maketitle

% =======================================================
% EXTENSIVE AND DETAILED ABSTRACT BASED ON YOUR PAPER
% =======================================================
\begin{abstract}
Educational institutions, particularly universities, increasingly rely on integrated databases and information systems to manage sensitive student records, administrative workflows, financial transactions, and academic services. However, this profound dependence on digital platforms exponentially exacerbates vulnerabilities to critical operational risks, such as destructive cyberattacks, unauthorized system access, unexpected service downtime, and catastrophic data loss. 

This research addresses these challenges by establishing a systematic security framework engineered for universities operating within stringent technical and financial constraints, utilizing Sana'a University as a baseline case study. The primary purpose of this quantitative and descriptive-analytical study is to assess, prioritize, and mitigate information security risks threatening critical institutional assets while simultaneously embedding operational resilience. 

To achieve this objective, the methodology deploys the structured OCTAVE Allegro risk assessment framework to prioritize information assets and evaluate potential threats based on a probability-impact matrix. Data were gathered through comprehensive interviews with university IT administrators and empirical reviews of system logs. 

The findings successfully identify the Student Database and Student Information System as highly exposed assets facing severe risk levels from ransomware attacks, unauthorized entry, and human errors. 

To counter these threats, an integrated protection model is designed, combining preventive measures with proactive data recovery mechanisms, including a strategic periodic backup schedule, the execution of the 3-2-1 backup rule, and a comprehensive Disaster Recovery Plan (DRP) targeting minimal service interruption. Ultimately, this integrated framework provides a scalable, low-cost solution that enhances incident response capabilities and operational continuity, offering a replicable blueprint for resource-limited academic institutions.
\end{abstract}

