\appendix
\section{OCTAVE Allegro Field Data Collection Instruments}
\label{app:octave_instruments}

\subsection{IT Administrator Interview Protocol}
The following standardized qualitative questionnaire was deployed during semi-structured interviews with IT administrators and network engineers at Sana'a University to define organizational boundaries and map core information assets[cite: 11]:
\begin{enumerate}
\item What primary information assets, databases, or application registries sustain daily student administration and grade documentation[cite: 11]?
\item What backup strategies (frequency, local medium, storage location) are currently implemented for the central SQL database instances[cite: 11]?
\item Detail the history of hardware server failures, power supply interruptions, or security incidents experienced by the university over the past 24 months[cite: 11].
\item What specific technical or financial operational boundaries restrict the deployment of advanced real-time remote data replication[cite: 11]?
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{OCTAVE Allegro Interactive Threat Profile Worksheet}
Table~\ref{tab:app_threat_worksheet} represents the field worksheet utilized to log threat scenarios, actors, motives, and immediate consequences during the Phase 2 analysis of the Student Database[cite: 11].

\begin{table}[htbp]
\caption{Asset-Centric Threat Profile Worksheet (Student Database)}
\label{tab:app_threat_worksheet}
\centering
\begin{tabular}{ll p{5cm} l}
\toprule
\textbf{Asset Name} & \textbf{Threat Actor} & \textbf{Threat Scenario / Vector} & \textbf{Direct Vulnerability Link} \\
\midrule
Student Database & External Hacker & Ransomware encryption of active transaction tables via unpatched application vulnerabilities[cite: 11]. & Outdated firewall and missing security patches[cite: 11]. \\
\addlinespace
Student Database & System Admin & Accidental deletion of operational schemas or tables due to lack of confirmation triggers[cite: 11]. & Missing access level restrictions and user error[cite: 11]. \\
\addlinespace
Student Database & System Crash & Simultaneous mechanical drive failure due to erratic power grid surges[cite: 11]. & Deficient uninterruptible power supply (UPS) systems[cite: 11]. \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\subsection{Disaster Recovery Verification Log Template}
The tactical checklist provided in Table~\ref{tab:app_drp_log} defines the operational layout used by technical teams to log recovery actions, verification outputs, and time signatures during a simulated system crash restoration process[cite: 5, 8, 11].

\begin{table}[htbp]
